17:05.458 --> 17:07.760
SAFE AND AFTERNOTE-- ALL OF THEM

17:07.760 --> 17:08.861
TRYING TO TACKLE WHAT IS

17:08.861 --> 17:10.663
BECOMING AN INCREASINGLY COMMON

17:10.663 --> 17:11.597
PROBLEM.

17:11.597 --> 17:13.332
>> NOWADAYS, EVERYONE KEEPS

17:13.332 --> 17:15.468
THEIR FILING CABINETS ON THEIR

17:15.468 --> 17:17.069
COMPUTERS, AND THEY MAY NOT HAVE

17:17.069 --> 17:18.771
SHARED THE ACCESS TO THAT WITH

17:18.771 --> 17:20.206
THEIR FAMILIES.

17:20.206 --> 17:21.107
>> Reporter: SUZANNE WALSH IS AN

17:21.107 --> 17:22.508
ESTATE LAWYER IN WEST HARTFORD,

17:22.508 --> 17:23.409
CONNECTICUT.

17:23.409 --> 17:24.677
>> I HAVE RECEIVED PANICKED

17:24.677 --> 17:27.480
CALLS FROM FAMILY MEMBERS WHO

17:27.480 --> 17:29.315
DON'T KNOW PASSWORDS, DON'T KNOW

17:29.315 --> 17:30.616
THE NATURE OF THE ONLINE

17:30.616 --> 17:31.284
ACCOUNTS.

17:31.284 --> 17:33.019
THEY SIMPLY KNOW MOM PAID THE

17:33.019 --> 17:34.620
BILLS ONLINE, AND THEY MAY NOT

17:34.620 --> 17:35.821
EVEN BE SURE ABOUT THE BANK.

17:35.821 --> 17:36.889
>> Reporter: WALSH SAYS THAT THE

17:36.889 --> 17:39.091
MAIN PROBLEM IS ONE OF ACCESS.

17:39.091 --> 17:40.326
IN MANY CASES, WE HAVE MADE IT

17:40.326 --> 17:42.395
VIRTUALLY ILLEGAL FOR ANYONE

17:42.395 --> 17:45.097
ELSE TO USE OUR ONLINE ACCOUNTS.

17:45.097 --> 17:46.032
IT STARTS WITH THOSE TERMS OF

17:46.032 --> 17:47.767
SERVICE AGREEMENTS, THE FINE

17:47.767 --> 17:50.036
PRINT OF THE ONLINE WORLD.

17:50.036 --> 17:51.437
ONCE THE "I AGREE" BUTTON IS

17:51.437 --> 17:52.939
PRESSED, IT'S AS GOOD AS A

17:52.939 --> 17:53.673
CONTRACT.

17:53.673 --> 17:55.841
>> MANY OF THEM PROHIBIT THE

17:55.841 --> 17:57.543
SHARING OF PASSWORDS, AND THEY

17:57.543 --> 17:59.412
PROHIBIT THIRD-PARTY ACCESS.

17:59.412 --> 18:01.480
SO, RIGHT NOW, THEY TEND TO BAR

18:01.480 --> 18:02.882
ANYBODY BUT THE ACCOUNT HOLDER

18:02.882 --> 18:04.116
ACCESSING THE ACCOUNT.

18:04.116 --> 18:05.618
>> Reporter: THAT MEANS EVEN IF

18:05.618 --> 18:07.620
THE ACCOUNT HOLDER IS DEAD.

18:07.620 --> 18:09.355
INTERNET SERVICE PROVIDERS SAY

18:09.355 --> 18:10.957
THEY'RE FOLLOWING THE LETTER OF

18:10.957 --> 18:12.558
THE LAW AS SPELLED OUT IN THE

18:12.558 --> 18:15.561
1986 STORED COMMUNICATIONS ACT,

18:15.561 --> 18:16.996
WHICH PROHIBITS ANYONE FROM

18:16.996 --> 18:18.297
ACCESSING PRIVATE INFORMATION

18:18.297 --> 18:20.499
ONLINE WITHOUT PERMISSION.

18:20.499 --> 18:21.867
>> THE PROBLEM WITH FIDUCIARY

18:21.867 --> 18:24.837
ACCESS NOW IS THAT IT MAY BE A

18:24.837 --> 18:26.806
VIOLATION OF FEDERAL PRIVACY LAW

18:26.806 --> 18:28.374
OR A COMPUTER FRAUD AND ABUSE

18:28.374 --> 18:28.908
ACT.

18:28.908 --> 18:30.977
IT MAY BE AN ACTUAL CRIMINAL ACT

18:30.977 --> 18:32.812
TO VIOLATE THE TERMS OF SERVICE

18:32.812 --> 18:33.512
AGREEMENT.

18:33.512 --> 18:34.547
>> Reporter: BUT BEING UNABLE TO

18:34.547 --> 18:36.282
ACCESS OR SHUT DOWN A DECEASED

18:36.282 --> 18:38.217
LOVED ONE'S ACCOUNTS COULD HAVE

18:38.217 --> 18:40.152
UNFORESEEN RISKS, AS GLENN

18:40.152 --> 18:41.554
WILLIAMSON, WHO SPENT 20 YEARS

18:41.554 --> 18:43.155
IN ONLINE SECURITY, WILL TELL

18:43.155 --> 18:43.756
YOU.

18:43.756 --> 18:45.257
>> THE YEAR AFTER SOMEBODY

18:45.257 --> 18:46.525
PASSES IS ONE OF THE MOST

18:46.525 --> 18:48.160
VULNERABLE TIMES FOR IDENTITY

18:48.160 --> 18:48.861
THEFT.

18:48.861 --> 18:50.329
IT'S A HEINOUS CRIME, BUT WHAT

18:50.329 --> 18:51.797
THE BAD GUYS DO, BECAUSE DEATH

18:51.797 --> 18:53.566
IS PUBLIC RECORD, THEY'LL GO OUT

18:53.566 --> 18:54.934
THERE AND THEY'LL COMB THROUGH

18:54.934 --> 18:56.902
RECENTLY DECEASED AND THEY'LL

18:56.902 --> 18:58.571
CREATE A FAKE IDENTITY BECAUSE

18:58.571 --> 19:00.306
THE DECEASED DON'T CHECK EMAILS

19:00.306 --> 19:01.741
AND THEY DON'T GET THE MAIL.

19:01.741 --> 19:02.641
>> Reporter: EVERY YEAR, MORE

19:02.641 --> 19:04.110
THAN TWO MILLION AMERICANS ARE

19:04.110 --> 19:05.578
THE POSTHUMOUS VICTIMS OF

19:05.578 --> 19:06.879
IDENTITY FRAUD.

19:06.879 --> 19:08.481
THIEVES CAN USE A DEAD PERSON'S

19:08.481 --> 19:09.949
INFORMATION TO RACK UP CREDIT

19:09.949 --> 19:12.284
CARD CHARGES, APPLY FOR LOANS OR

19:12.284 --> 19:14.754
EVEN FILE FALSE TAX RETURNS.

19:14.754 --> 19:16.222
AND MUCH OF THIS INFORMATION CAN

19:16.222 --> 19:17.590
BE FOUND ON THE INTERNET THROUGH

19:17.590 --> 19:19.158
SOMETHING AS SIMPLE AS A

19:19.158 --> 19:20.259
SHOPPING ACCOUNT.

19:20.259 --> 19:22.361
TO DATE, ONLY SEVEN STATES HAVE

19:22.361 --> 19:24.063
ANY LAWS IN EFFECT THAT GOVERN

19:24.063 --> 19:26.032
ONLINE ESTATE PLANNING.

19:26.032 --> 19:27.199
SUZANNE WALSH, WHO CHAIRS A

19:27.199 --> 19:28.934
COMMITTEE ON THE UNIFORM LAW

19:28.934 --> 19:30.236
COMMISSION, AN ORGANIZATION

19:30.236 --> 19:32.171
WHICH DRAFTS LAWS WHICH IT HOPES

19:32.171 --> 19:33.973
TO STANDARDIZE IN ALL 50 STATES,

19:33.973 --> 19:35.674
IS HOPING TO CHANGE THAT.

19:35.674 --> 19:38.110
OVER THE PAST TWO YEARS, WALSH'S

19:38.110 --> 19:39.311
COMMITTEE HAS BEEN DRAFTING THE

19:39.311 --> 19:41.580
FIDUCIARY ACCESS TO DIGITAL

19:41.580 --> 19:43.649
ASSETS ACT, WHICH WOULD GIVE

19:43.649 --> 19:44.984
FIDUCIARIES THE SAME RIGHTS OVER

19:44.984 --> 19:47.353
ONLINE ESTATES AS THEY NOW HAVE

19:47.353 --> 19:49.088
OVER PHYSICAL ESTATES.

19:49.088 --> 19:50.189
>> FIDUCIARIES, TRADITIONALLY,

19:50.189 --> 19:51.557
HAVE ACCESS TO EVERYTHING IN

19:51.557 --> 19:52.925
ADMIN... ESPECIALLY IN

19:52.925 --> 19:54.360
ADMINISTERING ESTATES.

19:54.360 --> 19:55.828
AND THAT USED TO MEAN OPENING UP

19:55.828 --> 19:57.430
THE MAILBOX, OPENING UP THE FILE

19:57.430 --> 19:58.831
CABINET, RIFLING THROUGH THE

19:58.831 --> 19:59.665
DESK.

19:59.665 --> 20:01.967
OUR ACT IS DESIGNED TO CONTINUE

20:01.967 --> 20:04.303
THAT AND FACILITATE THAT, GIVEN

20:04.303 --> 20:05.371
THE DIFFERENT NATURE OF THE

20:05.371 --> 20:06.372
DIGITAL ASSETS.

20:06.372 --> 20:07.073
>> Reporter: THE BILL WAS

20:07.073 --> 20:08.174
REVIEWED AND ENACTED BY THE

20:08.174 --> 20:10.342
UNIFORM LAW COMMISSION THIS PAST

20:10.342 --> 20:11.243
JULY.

20:11.243 --> 20:12.311
BUT IT'S STILL UP TO INDIVIDUAL

20:12.311 --> 20:14.080
STATE LEGISLATURES TO PROPOSE IT

20:14.080 --> 20:15.948
AND PASS IT AS LAW.

20:15.948 --> 20:17.283
AS OF NOW, ONLY ONE STATE,

20:17.283 --> 20:19.251
DELAWARE, HAS SIGNED THE ACT

20:19.251 --> 20:20.186
INTO LAW.

20:20.186 --> 20:21.620
EVEN SO, THE NEW LAW HAS FACED

20:21.620 --> 20:22.988
OPPOSITION.

20:22.988 --> 20:23.823
THE GENERAL COUNSEL OF A

20:23.823 --> 20:25.724
WASHINGTON, D.C.-BASED GROUP

20:25.724 --> 20:27.393
CALLED THE STATE PRIVACY AND

20:27.393 --> 20:28.928
SECURITY COALITION, WHICH

20:28.928 --> 20:29.929
REPRESENTS THE INTERESTS OF

20:29.929 --> 20:31.597
GOOGLE, YAHOO AND FACEBOOK,

20:31.597 --> 20:33.099
AMONG OTHERS, HAS COME OUT

20:33.099 --> 20:35.701
AGAINST THE BILL SAYING, "THIS

20:35.701 --> 20:37.570
LAW TAKES NO ACCOUNT OF

20:37.570 --> 20:39.004
MINIMIZING INTRUSIONS INTO THE

20:39.004 --> 20:41.273
PRIVACY OF THIRD PARTIES WHO

20:41.273 --> 20:42.842
COMMUNICATED WITH THE DECEASED.

20:42.842 --> 20:44.443
THIS WOULD INCLUDE HIGHLY

20:44.443 --> 20:46.045
CONFIDENTIAL COMMUNICATIONS TO

20:46.045 --> 20:47.880
DECEDENTS FROM THIRD PARTIES WHO

20:47.880 --> 20:49.315
ARE STILL ALIVE, WHO WOULD BE

20:49.315 --> 20:51.517
VERY SURPRISED THAT AN EXECUTOR

20:51.517 --> 20:52.451
IS REVIEWING THE

20:52.451 --> 20:53.819
COMMUNICATIONS."

20:53.819 --> 20:55.254
BUT, DESPITE THE PUSHBACK,

20:55.254 --> 20:56.755
SUZANNE WALSH IS HOPEFUL THAT

20:56.755 --> 20:58.090
HER COMMITTEE'S WORK WILL BE

20:58.090 --> 20:59.291
RECOGNIZED IN MORE STATE

20:59.291 --> 21:00.559
LEGISLATURES.

21:00.559 --> 21:02.461
>> WIDESPREAD ENACTMENT IS OUR

21:02.461 --> 21:03.129
GOAL.

21:03.129 --> 21:04.363
THAT'S OUR PRIMARY GOAL.

21:04.363 --> 21:05.631
CERTAINLY WE HOPE AND EXPECT

21:05.631 --> 21:07.600
THAT IT WON'T TAKE MORE THAN A

21:07.600 --> 21:09.335
YEAR OR TWO FOR MOST OF THE

21:09.335 --> 21:11.003
STATES TO ADOPT THIS PRODUCT.

21:11.003 --> 21:11.770
>> Reporter: FOR NOW, THERE ARE

21:11.770 --> 21:13.239
STEPS THAT PEOPLE CAN TAKE

21:13.239 --> 21:14.840
TO MAKE THE PROCESS OF DIGITAL

21:14.840 --> 21:16.976
ESTATE MANAGEMENT EASIER ON NEXT

21:16.976 --> 21:17.843
OF KIN.

21:17.843 --> 21:20.212
FIRST, CREATE AN INVENTORY LIST

21:20.212 --> 21:21.847
OF ALL YOUR ONLINE ACCOUNTS AND

21:21.847 --> 21:24.016
PASSWORDS FOR YOUR FIDUCIARY.

21:24.016 --> 21:25.417
STIPULATE WHAT TO DO WITH YOUR

21:25.417 --> 21:27.553
EMAIL ACCOUNTS IN A WILL, AND

21:27.553 --> 21:29.221
READ THE TERMS OF SERVICE

21:29.221 --> 21:30.322
AGREEMENTS SO YOU CAN

21:30.322 --> 21:32.424
UNDERSTAND HOW OR EVEN IF

21:32.424 --> 21:34.260
ACCESS TO YOUR ACCOUNTS CAN BE

21:34.260 --> 21:35.928
GRANTED TO SOMEONE ELSE.

21:35.928 --> 21:37.863
BUT GLENN WILLIAMSON SAYS, NO

21:37.863 --> 21:39.765
MATTER WHAT STEPS YOU TAKE OR

21:39.765 --> 21:41.367
WHAT LAWS ARE EVENTUALLY PASSED,

21:41.367 --> 21:43.068
MANAGING A DIGITAL ESTATE FOR A

21:43.068 --> 21:45.404
LOVED ONE WILL ALWAYS BE A LONG,

21:45.404 --> 21:47.907
ARDUOUS AND PAINFUL PROCESS.

21:49.808 --> 21:50.676
>> Sreenivasan: TO LEARN HOW TO

21:50.676 --> 21:51.844
BETTER MANAGE YOUR OWN DIGITAL

21:51.844 --> 21:55.080
ESTATE, VISIT newshour.pbs.org.

21:56.615 --> 21:57.416
>> Sreenivasan: FINALLY

